                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2314a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ramer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-09T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Department is informed that about 200 armed Honduranean political refugees
                    are making depredations on Honduran border districts and have robbed towns of
                    Paraiso, San Antonio de Flores and Duyure. Make urgent representations to
                    Nicaraguan Government in order that it may stop the activities of this band and
                    reconcentrate the leaders.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
